==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*kuningaz'', perhaps from a suffixed form of an Indo-European base ''*gen-'' ‘procreate’ (Latin [[genus]], English [[kin]]).  The original meaning may be ‘leader of people’ or ‘noble-born’.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[kuning]] (Dutch [[koning]]), Old High German [[kuning]] (German [[König]]), Old Norse [[konungr]] (Swedish [[konung]]).

